A man was found guilty of murder for causing a Los Angeles train crash that killed 11 people.
The jury recommended life in prison without parole, rejecting the death penalty.
Prosecutors argued that the man staged the accident to get attention from his wife.
Defense claimed his troubled childhood and meth addiction led to delusions.
The crash resulted in 11 deaths and 180 injuries.
The man apologized, stating he never intended harm.
Family members testified about his abusive upbringing.
The jury deliberates between life in prison or execution.
The man's mother tearfully recounted years of abuse by her husband.
